                <head>No. 134.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hoffman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-05-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 27, 1876</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram received. Sir Edward Thornton has read to me one from Lord Derby,
                    stating that you had proposed to him the negotiation of the additional
                    article.</p>
                <p>You will please inform me immediately whether the suggestion proceeded in the
                    first instance from you or from him, and if from him, how far you may have
                    encouraged it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FISH, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
